SIMPLE: mulct
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mulct
<hw>Mulct</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>mulcta</ets>,
<ets>multa</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A fine or penalty, esp. a
pecuniary punishment or penalty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A blemish or defect.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Amercement; forfeit; forfeiture;
penalty.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mulct</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mulct
<hw>Mulct</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Mulcted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Mulcting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>mulctare</ets>,
<ets>multare</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To punish for an offense or
misdemeanor by imposing a fine or forfeiture, esp. a pecuniary fine; to
fine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, to deprive of; to withhold by way of
punishment or discipline.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mulctuary</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Mulctary</ent>⟦br⟧
